nt, most likely you have had this issue: You install source files in Windows format in your Unix environment.</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"paragraph\">\n<p>There is a way quite simple to convert all your files from Windows to Unix format:</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"listingblock\">\n<div class=\"content\">\n<pre class=\"highlight\"><code class=\"language-bash\" data-lang=\"bash\">find . -<span class=\"hljs-built_in\">type</span> f -print0 | xargs -0 dos2unix</code></pre>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"paragraph\">\n<p>I got it, of course, form <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/11929461/how-can-i-run-dos2unix-on-an-entire-directory\" class=\"bare\">https://stackoverflow.com/questions/11929461/how-can-i-run-dos2unix-on-an-entire-directory</a></p>\n</div>","slug":"recursive-dos-unix"}